  "prompt": "Does India contribute to the ISS (International Space Station)?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, India is not a primary partner in the International Space Station (ISS) program like the United States, Russia, Europe, Canada, and Japan are. However, India has shown interest in human spaceflight and has developed its own capabilities through the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO).\n\nIndia has participated in various collaborative space initiatives, and while it does not have a permanent presence on the ISS, ISRO has expressed interest in potentially collaborating on human spaceflight missions. In recent years, India has been working on its Gaganyaan mission, which aims to send Indian astronauts into space. This mission may involve interactions with international space programs.\n\nStill, as of the latest information, India does not contribute to the ISS project directly, but it actively participates in the global space community and contributes through its own missions and projects.",
